                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.119/277: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-02T15:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received July 2, 3.05 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Navy Department has made a contract with Japanese firm for the purchase of arms
                    and ammunition. Alleging necessity of suppressing piracy, Chinese Government
                    asks for raising of arms embargo. General opinion is no change should be made as
                    yet.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
